title: Koadic
extract: n an island off southern Alaska in the Gulf of Alaska; site of the first European settlement in the area which was founded by the Russians in 1784. Synonyms: Kodiak Island Example of: island. a land mass (smaller than a continent) that is surrounded by water. 2.
